  "id": "019cdcdc-fd00-7850-9bc2-a2a445babf43",
  "content": "    # CUDA\n\n### Task 5: Add CUDA awareness to rebuild command\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `.devcontainer/scripts/corvia-workspace.sh`\n\nThe file is at: `/root/corvia-project/corvia-workspace/.devcontainer/scripts/corvia-workspace.sh`\n\n**Step 1: Update `rebuild_binaries()` to pass `--features cuda` when enabled**\n\nReplace the existing `rebuild_binaries()` function with:\n\n```bash\nrebuild_binaries() {\n    echo \"Rebuilding Corvia binaries from local source...\"\n\n    local corvia_src=\"$WORKSPACE_ROOT/repos/corvia\"\n\n    if [ ! -d \"$corvia_src\" ]; then\n        echo \"  Error: corvia source not found at $corvia_src\"\n        exit 1\n    fi\n\n    cd \"$corvia_src\"\n    cargo install --path crates/corvia-cli\n\n    if [ \"$(get_flag cuda)\" = \"enabled\" ]; then\n        echo \"  Building corvia-inference with CUDA support...\"\n        cargo install --path crates/corvia-inference --features cuda\n        cp \"$(which corvia-inference)\" /usr/local/bin/corvia-inference-cuda\n    else\n        cargo install --path crates/corvia-inference\n    fi\n    cd \"$WORKSPACE_ROOT\"\n\n    echo \"  Binaries rebuilt from local source.\"\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Verify the script parses correctly**\n\nRun: `bash -n /root/corvia-project/corvia-workspace/.devcontainer/scripts/corvia-workspace.sh`\nExpected: no output (success)\n\n**Step 3: Commit**\n\n```bash\ncd /root/corvia-project/corvia-workspace\ngit add .devcontainer/scripts/corvia-workspace.sh\ngit commit -m \"feat: rebuild command respects cuda flag for GPU-enabled builds\"\n```\n\n---\n",
